<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' CHOICE: WHAT MAD PURSUIT: A PERSONAL VIEW OF SCIENTIFIC DISCOVERY BY 
FRANCIS CRICK (BASIC BOOKS: $16.95; 182 PP.) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Lee Dembart 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"What Mad Pursuit" is "Crick's version of the crucial events" in the discovery 
of DNA. "An elegant exposition that concentrates almost entirely on ideas. It 
is about how science is done." Lee Dembart 
</P>
