<HEADLINE>
<P>
PIRANHAS AFTER 'BRAZIL' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shame. I've seen films ruined before by studio executives, but Universal 
Studios' televised version of "Brazil" takes the cake (Outtakes item, by Steven 
Smith, Jan. 8)! 
</P>
<P>
It is ironic that film maker Terry Gilliam, whose chief idea was to warn us of 
"the system," should lose out in the end to the Big Brother of Universal. 
</P>
<P>
But the real losers are those who see this movie for the first time and think 
this version -- which has undergone changes in editing, the musical score, 
dialogue and the ending -- is the real thing. 
</P>
<P>
Bah humbug! What a way to start the new year. 
</P>
<P>
GREGORY NERI 
</P>
<P>
Manhattan Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
