KITCHELL CONTRACTORS TO RENOVATE RESORT IN PALM SPRINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kitchell Contractors, Irvine, has been selected to carry out the $15-million 
renovation of the Radisson Palm Springs Resort and Conference Center in Palm 
Springs. 
</P>
<P>
The hotel, built in 1960, is owned by Home Federal Savings &amp; Loan of San 
Diego and operated by Radisson Hotel Corp., based in Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
Phased renovations of the guest rooms, with exterior and new interior 
improvements designed by architect is Arechaederra Hong Treiman of Santa 
Monica, are scheduled for completion in the spring. 
</P>
