<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAR DEALER OLSEN SELLS ENCINO SITE SITE TO DEVELOPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
High land values have helped push Porsches and Audis off Ventura Boulevard in 
Encino. 
</P>
<P>
Ground will be broken tomorrow at the former Merlin Olson Porsche/Audi 
dealership at 15493-15503 Ventura Blvd. for the $20-million, 3-story Encino 
Spectrum retail and office building. 
</P>
<P>
"Land prices that are now exceeding $100 a square foot and limitations on high 
rises have made upscale retailers and offices for professionals the best use of 
the land," says Tony Dorn, of Beitler Commercial Realty Services, who is 
representing the developers Yehuda Netanel and Morris Ishaaya of West Los 
Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
