<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALUABLE MING POTTERY MISSING FROM MUSEUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By UPI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COLUMBUS, Ohio 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 550-year-old Ming bowl that looks like a cereal bowl but is valued at 
$250,000 is missing from the Columbus Museum of Art, police said. Lloyd's of 
London is offering a $25,000 reward for information leading to the arrest and 
conviction of whoever stole the bowl, which was discovered missing Friday. 
</P>
