<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIBERY AFFAIR TURNS UP NEWPORT HERO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange Countians have a renewed confidence in the strength of their American 
democracy and Newport Beach citizens have a new hero in their midst with the 
story (Jan. 5) of the courageous service provided by Newport's Planning 
Commission chairman, Buzz Person, in derailing the attempt by a local 
restaurant owner to subvert the democratic process of our government through 
bribery. Such undercover corruption gnaws at the very vitals of American 
democracy. But to know we have a public servant with guts and integrity who 
could call this illegal and unpatriotic attempt on its own ground, gives us all 
hope and new faith in America. 
</P>
<P>
Newporters have reason to be proud of their community, and we all have a new 
hero -- Buzz Person! 
</P>
<P>
If there is a cloud in the affair, it is the tap-on-the-wrist sentence on the 
perpetrator by Judge Margaret Anderson. If a judge does not understand any 
better the threat to America that lack of integrity in government brings, then 
she should get off the bench. 
</P>
<P>
TOM PENDELL 
</P>
<P>
Balboa 
</P>
</TEXT>
