<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE HOT PURSUITS AND LOSS OF LIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We were very saddened to read about the tragic deaths of Jessica Warren and 
Dawn Hammond, victims of the police pursuit on Christmas morning. 
</P>
<P>
We were saddened not only because we know of the sorrow of the family and 
friends, but because the circumstances might have been prevented had a jury 
voted to find the Costa Mesa police guilty in their pursuit of Ruben Valle on 
Dec. 12, 1984. We believe that the "not guilty" decision gave a green light to 
Orange County law enforcement that hot pursuits will be condoned or even 
encouraged at the expense of an innocent public. 
</P>
<P>
It was our son and brother, along with Billy Dearing, who lost their lives as 
innocent victims Dec. 12, 1984. We were outraged then and are outraged now that 
hot pursuits still claim the lives of the innocent. Although police departments 
have "guidelines," guidelines are not law and don't have to be followed. We 
tried to bring this macho law enforcement attitude to the public's attention 
through our lawsuit, and it was an uphill battle for the better part of 3 
years. 
</P>
<P>
It is our hope and prayer that one day law enforcement will have to be 
accountable for acts of irresponsibility in the line of duty. 
</P>
<P>
KEITH WILLIAMSON 
</P>
<P>
SHARON WILLIAMSON 
</P>
<P>
MERRITT WILLIAMSON 
</P>
<P>
DEIDRE WILLIAMSON 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa 
</P>
</TEXT>
