<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Carole Merle of France ended a Swiss 13-race victory streak by winning a World 
Cup women's super giant slalom at Grindelwald, Switzerland. 
</P>
<P>
Merle covered the hard-packed course in 1 minute 26.24 seconds, well ahead of 
the 1:27.97 posted by runner-up Sigrid Wolf of Austria. 
</P>
<P>
Merle, 24, is the only non-Swiss winner on the women's circuit this winter. The 
Swiss have won every event since Merle's victory in the season-opening super-G 
last November. 
</P>
