<HEADLINE>
<P>
WCAC ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
PORTLAND BEATS SAN DIEGO, 57-54, TO END LOSING STREAK AT 21 GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Portland snapped the NCAA Division I's longest losing streak at 21 games 
Saturday night with a 57-54 victory over the University of San Diego at San 
Diego. 
</P>
<P>
The Pilots' last victory came against San Diego last Feb. 6 at Portland. 
</P>
<P>
Portland is 1-14 overall and 1-1 in the West Coast Athletic Conference. San 
Diego fell to 5-9 and 0-2 after its fourth consecutive loss. 
</P>
<P>
Bart Koenitzer made 2 baskets, including a 5-foot turnaround jumper with 1:30 
left that put the Pilots ahead for good, 55-54. 
</P>
<P>
St. Mary's 67, Gonzaga 45 -- Erick Newman and James Dailey each scored 15 
points to pace the Gaels to victory at Moraga, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
Gonzaga pulled within 6 points with 11:18 left, 45-39, but the Gaels scored 16 
straight points, 7 by Newman, to put the game away. 
</P>
<P>
St. Mary's (14-1 overall and 2-0 in the WCAC) out-rebounded the Bulldogs (10-5, 
1-1), 37-21. 
</P>
</TEXT>
